ame": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2019-09-11T13:48:53Z", "updated_at": "2019-10-05T10:45:37Z", "closed_at": "2019-10-05T10:45:37Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Dear all,\r\n\r\nI'm writing a small TCP-based time-measuring tool and use the `std::net::TcpStream`. It turned out that I want to manipulate additional options via `setsockopt()`, but this is not available in the \r\nstable API of https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/master/src/libstd/net/tcp.rs.\r\n\r\nHowever, in https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/tree/master/src/libstd/sys_common, the raw `setsockopt()` method is exposed and it would be straightforward to add support for more options.\r\n\r\nNow my question is what's the best and most straightforward way to add it---both locally for me and also for the community. I have checked the `CONTRIBUTING.md` guide, but as I want to fiddle around with libstd, I am not sure if I should do an RFC or a PR (and what's the best practise of local libstd modification).\r\n\r\nI would be happy to contribute additional TCP-interfacing code to the community, but I would probably need some more guidance from experienced Rustaceans.\r\n\r\nThanks in advance!", "closed_by": {"login": "netzdoktor", "id": 974093, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjk3NDA5Mw==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/974093?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/netzdoktor", "html_url": "https://github.com/netzdoktor", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/netzdoktor/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/netzdoktor/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/netzdoktor/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/netzdoktor/starred{/owner}